<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="SB0052" sponsor="Lincoln Fillmore" designation="SB" otherSponsor="Tracy J. Miller" otherHouse="House" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL0859" date="12/29/2025 12:12:347" printDate="12-29 12:23" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>3</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="05/06/2026"><seclist><sect action="A" src="code" buid="1" uid="C53E-6-S901_2026050620260506" fromuid="C53E-6-S901_2024050120240501" sort="53E06 09010020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">53E-6-901</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="2" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Substitute Teaching Requirements Amendments</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Lincoln Fillmore</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>House Sponsor: Tracy J. Miller</otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill removes the requirement for a teaching license for a long-term substitute.</gd><hphead lineno="6">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="7" slineno="0-7">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8" level="1">removes the requirement for a teaching license for a long-term substitute.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="10">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="12">None</ocNone><sa numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saamd numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14"><snhead>AMENDS:</snhead><sn num="53E-6-901" src="code" uid="C53E-6-S901_2026050620260506" buid="1" sort="53E06 09010020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="15" slineno="0-15"><bold>53E-6-901</bold>, as last amended by Laws of Utah 2024, Chapter 22</sn></saamd></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="16"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="17" slineno="0-17">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="53E-6-901" type="amend" src="code" uid="C53E-6-S901_2026050620260506" sort="53E06 09010020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section number="53E-6-901" numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="1-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="18">Section 1. Section <bold>53E-6-901</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="19"><bold>53E-6-901<parens/>. Substitute teachers.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-null-1" dnum="1-o" numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="1-3" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display>(1)</display>As used in this section, "substitute teacher" means a licensed or non-licensed individual <ln numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="1-4"/>who is employed by a school district to fill in for a regular classroom teacher during the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="1-5"/>teacher's temporary absence from the classroom.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-2" dnum="2-o" numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="1-6" level="1"><display>(2)</display>When hiring substitute teachers, school districts shall prioritize licensed educators as <ln numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-7"/>substitutes when available.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-3" dnum="3-o" numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-8" level="1"><display>(3)</display>An individual shall submit to a background check in accordance with Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="53G-11-402"><ln numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-9"/>53G-11-402</xref> prior to employment as a substitute teacher.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-4" dnum="4-o:_-i" numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-10" ea="erase" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="2" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1003" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="start">(4)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="3" groupid="2" style="2" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" deltag="end">A teacher's position in the classroom may not be filled by a non-licensed substitute <ln numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-11"/>teacher for more than a total of 20 days during any school year unless a licensed <ln numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-12"/>educator is not available.</amend><amendoutend style="2"/></subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-5" dnum="5-o:4-i" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-13" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1004" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(5)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(4)</amend></display>An individual who is ineligible to hold a license for reasons described in Title <xref depth="2" refnumber="53E-6-6">53E, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-14"/>Chapter 6, Part 6</xref>, License Denial and Discipline, may not serve as a substitute teacher.</subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="2" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="32">Section 2.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="33"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="5/6/2026">May 6, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>12-29-25 12:23 PM</tm></rev></foot></leg>